  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 400°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and chop <strong>potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces </p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half </p>\n<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic </strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>portobello mushrooms</strong> and <strong>halved tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> to a baking tray </p>\n<p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and tender</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat without draining</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong></p>\n<p>Finely chop the <strong>coriander</strong>, including the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>shallot</strong> to a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and grind to a paste</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chilli flakes</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and mix to combine</p>\n<p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>chimichurri</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once <span class=\"text-highlight\">the mushrooms and tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> are</span> cooked, add the <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> to the tray</p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven and cook for a further 2-4 min or until the <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> are golden and toasted</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cannellini beans</strong> (no need to drain) <span class=\"text-highlight\">to the pot of <strong>cooked potatoes</strong></span></p>\n<p>Return the pan to a high heat and cook for 2-3 min or until the beans are warmed through, then drain the lot</p>\n<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash together until smooth – this is your <strong>cannellini bean mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-portobellos-garlic-bean-mash-and-chimichurri/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong> roasted portobello mushrooms</strong></span> and <strong>tomato</strong> with the <strong>cannellini bean mash</strong> and <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong> to the side </p>\n<p>Sprinkle the <strong>toasted pumpkin seeds </strong>over the <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle over the <strong>chimichurri</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
